Class Match

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.SocScore.framework.data.Match

  • public class Match
extends java.lang.Object
    Object representing an instance of a match, and all its relevant information.
    See Also:
    LeagueAnalysis, LiveInput, BatchInput

    • Constructor Detail

      • Match

        public Match(Team team1,
             Team team2)
        Initializes a new instance of match, and adds the inputted teams to the match. This constructor assumes the match has yet to happen.
        Parameters:
        team1 - First team to be added to the new match.
        team2 - Second team to be added to the new match.
        See Also:
        LiveInput

      • Match

        public Match(Team team1,
             Team team2,
             java.time.LocalDateTime startTime,
             java.time.LocalDateTime endTime)
        Initializes a new instance of a match, and adds the teams to the match, as well as the start and end time. This constructor assumes a match has already happened, and therefore sets the match's status as ended.
        Parameters:
        team1 - First team to be added to the new match.
        team2 - Second team to be added to the new match.
        startTime - Time at which the match began.
        endTime - Time at which the match ended.

    • Method Detail

      • resetTeams

        void resetTeams()
        Used by LeagueAnalysis.loadLeagueFromDisk() to perform re-linking teams and matches after a data load.

      • startMatch

        public void startMatch(java.time.LocalDateTime startTime)
                throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Starts a new match, sets the match to active, stores the start time, and calls Team.startMatch() on both teams.
        Parameters:
        startTime - The time at which the match started.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - Throws an exception if the match has already started, or has already ended.

      • endMatch

        public void endMatch(java.time.LocalDateTime endTime)
              throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Ends a currently happening match, stores the end time, and updates the score for both teams.
        Parameters:
        endTime - Time at which the match ended.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - Throws an exception if a match that hasn't started tries to be ended.
        See Also:
        updateScore()

      • updateScore

        public void updateScore()
        Determines which team has won the game, stores it in a field, and sends this information over to both teams so they can update their respective fields.
        See Also:
        Team.endMatch(int, int)

      • incrementTeamScore

        public void incrementTeamScore(int TEAM_ID)
                        throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Increments the score of the appropriate Team by 1.
        Parameters:
        TEAM_ID - ID of the team who's score to increment.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - Throws an exception if it is attempted to increment the score of a team not in the match.
